<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id6b103bbe-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s59s"><num value="59s">§ 59s.</num><heading> Green River, Washington</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">For the purposes of <ref href="/us/usc/t33/s401">section 401 of this title</ref>, the portion of the Green River in the State of Washington lying upstream from that State Highway 516 bridge which is in existence on <date date="1981-10-26">October 26, 1981</date>, is hereby declared to be not a navigable waterway.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id6b103bbf-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">(<ref href="/us/pl/97/68/s2/b">Pub. L. 97–68, § 2(b)</ref>, <date date="1981-10-26">Oct. 26, 1981</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/95/1040">95 Stat. 1040</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
